title: Former Recreation Lead at FOUNDATION FOR SENIOR LIVING PROGRAMS
summary:
I am a freelance Graphic Artist and was a Chef and now I’m a home decor designer, gallery artist and illustrator.

I been working as a Chef and illustrator for 10 years. This experience has given me the expertise needed to work with a various array of clients.


I take pride in everything that I create and I am a task orintated worker.

As a youngster I participated in the Mayor Daley's Summer Youth program for emerging Chicago Artist in 1972. The Program focused on mentoring  Chicago's inner city youth from ages 10-15.
My job duties included painting murals  for the beautification of inner urban area.
On march 1st 2011  I Participated in the Oakland Street Flea Market Atlanta ga.

Art institute of Phoenix Arizona
At this location I won the campus Digital  Art Gallery Poster contest at the Art Institute of Phoenix for my illustration " The Power of Arizona" on April 2013. I did not complete the BA program but received college credit for my 2 1/2 years of education.

In april 2012 I was  Accepted into the program for Graphic Designers with a focus on illustration.



April 2011 I worked as a Artist liason at Greenbriar Mall for kids brunch event  Atlanta ga

May 2011 Participated as a artist liason in the Black Arts Festival at Greenbrial Mall Atlanta Ga.

June 2011 My Artwork  was featured in Frozen Magazine publication.  In the "Summer Wonder Edition of Frozen Magazine Atlanta Ga you can view my Art entries online.

member_awards_collection.title: letter of Recommendation
member_awards_collection.issuer: Instructor Ami King, Art Institute of Phoenix Arizona
member_awards_collection.description:
20 January 2014

Winston Harrell was a student in my “monster” literature class at the Art Institute of Phoenix, Winter 2013. He was very involved in class discussion and was a team player during group work and smaller group discussions. He made valuable contributions and interesting comments, adding to a very lively class atmosphere. Winston is also very good at multitasking and helping others. When Winston has knowledge that others do not, he is happy to share. He has a very creative mind, a keen eye for design and very good drawing skills. His werewolf drawings and paintings for the monster class included the major topics/themes of the course: monsters, self and the hideous other using the stages of man morphing into werewolf. His cross-disciplinary skills with art are fantastic.

Winston’s also has a full and lush style to his art, using rich colors and ripe imagery. I recommend his art and his conceptualization—especially his ability to flesh out complex ideas by hand on paper.

Sincerely,

Ami H. King
Adjunct Professor
Art Institute of Phoenix
Ami King <ahk@q.com

member_experience_collection.title: Graphic Artist
member_experience_collection.description:
To Whom It May Concern:

I would like to provide a reference and recommendation for Winston Harrell. I am a professional in the Graphic Design industry and an instructor for the Westwood College Graphic Design Department.
The extent of my acquaintance with Mr. Harrell has been through his class with me in Multimedia Presentations with Flash (GD251) and Digital Layout (GD131). During that time Mr. Harrell exemplified a great level of creativity in his conceptualization of design projects. I am in touch with Mr. Harrell on an on-going basis and was able to witness his progress throughout his stay at Westwood. His ideas are grand and colorful and anyone can run with his original visual creations and end with a fabulous result.
Mr. Harrell has great vision, determination and patience as it relates to completing tasks. He is confident in his ability to grasp use of tools and software available to execute a design yet humble enough to ask for advice and assistance. He has also proven to be highly professional and helpful in his critique and cooperation with fellow learners. His professional attitude toward learning and the design industry is a level above many of his colleagues and he can be depended on to follow through. These qualities suite him well and are fitting for a creative leader/director as well as a team member in a creative support environment.
Should you have further inquiry, don’t hesitate to contact me.

Regards,

Tanacha Brown, M.S.
designertee@ymail.com

My main focus is to create a pattern that will be aesthetically pleasing to the buyer while using my skills as Artist to visually enhance the image. To complete this task I mainly use Adobe programs illustrator CS6 and Photoshop CS6. I also use Acrylic paints and brushes to create patterns and later manipulate them in Photoshop while paying close attention to file size and image pixilization.
This is a part time endeavor at the moment but could turn into a full time job.
